HEADWORD: Inoceramus
<hw>In`o*cer"a*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'i`s</grk>, <grk>'ino`s</grk>, a muscle + <?/ an earthen
vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of large,
fossil, bivalve shells, allied to the mussels. The genus is
characteristic of the Cretaceous period.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

